content:
Deprecated ("old") routes should be scheduled for removal (like 6 months max after the new version +1 lands, 12 months max after the new version lands)

Adding enums to old versions to make them match new version CAN crash an app, the same way as removing the old version would. If your enum is stored as a column in a DB, the new enum can't be stored in the DB.
Removing those versions will have the same effect for the client dev, but request a correct update from him  (update path) instead of the half-assed "ignore that enum" and require less work for you.

content:
so now I've tried two times for 6 hours to find anything in the warzone >= cruiser to drop on to test my Sins ....
it started with me camping the IHubs, but sadly I could only watch as @Blood Raider Goomb killed some random stuff.
Then Balls Deep logged out a Cyno at the iHub and formed retries which I thought about dropping but decided against it, so I switched to another Ihub where Balls Deep were sitting in a Bait Domi Navy....
After some hours I was bored so I switched to MinMil comms where they said 2 Astartes and 2 Oneiros are gatecamping in Auga/Ama.
So I move over there just to find Balls Deep in 10 Tornados. I warped to Ama gate at 0 and wanted to see if they lock the Arazu... yes they did, I clicked jump but they deleted me before the Jump was executed ðŸ’€
So then I burn to Rens to reship and go to Egmar area where I am super lucky to find a small cruiser gang. 1 Vaga, 1 Scythe Fleet, 1 Scythe....
I disrupt the Vaga and they aggress me... everything is cool now... except for I forgot the fuel to open the cyno .... so I just feed another arazu...
now I buy a third one and decide to drop on a Gatecamp in Starkman. Finally it all works, but my PC almost crashes jumping in and the phantasm and the other stuff gets away. <_<
Then AmarrMil tries to bait me out with a Tempest + Geddon but I don't take the bait. I almost did because I was so frustrated.
Then I camped Vard where the FL33T station was reffed. In case of a fight, maybe I could third party on something... but nobody showed up and no fight happened.
In between I also camped an Amarr supply depot hoping some exeq navy would show up but nothing....

Blopsing is not as cool as I thought ðŸ’€ My goal was to kill one cruiser or bigger in the warzone... and I failed... could have just undocked a Bellicose or Thrasher Fleet and get more fun ðŸ˜¢
